{"title_page": "1960 Buenos Aires Grand Prix", "text_new": "{{Infobox Grand Prix race report\n|Type           = \n|Country        = ARG\n|Grand Prix     = Buenos Aires\n|Details ref    =\n|Date           = 14 February\n|Year           = 1960\n|Official name  = XIII Gran Premio Ciudad de Buenos Aires\n|Location       = [[C\u00f3rdoba Province, Argentina|Cordoba Province]]\n|Course         = Parque Sarmiento\n|Course_mi      = 1.926\n|Course_km      = 3.100\n|Distance_laps  = 75\n|Distance_mi    = 144.450\n|Distance_km    = 232.478\n|Weather        =\n|Attendance     =\n|Pole_Driver    = [[Jack Brabham]]\n|Pole_Country   = Australia\n|Pole_Team      = [[Cooper Car Company|Cooper]]-[[Coventry Climax|Climax]]\n|Pole_Time      = 1:27.3\n|Fast_Driver    = [[Bruce McLaren]]\n|Fast_Team      = [[Cooper Car Company|Cooper]]-[[Coventry Climax|Climax]]\n|Fast_Time      = 1:27.2\n|Fast_Lap       =\n|Fast_Country   = New Zealand\n|First_Driver   = [[Maurice Trintignant]]\n|First_Country  = France\n|First_Team     = [[Cooper Car Company|Cooper]]-[[Coventry Climax|Climax]]\n|Second_Driver  = [[Dan Gurney]]\n|Second_Country = USA\n|Second_Team    = [[BRM]]\n|Third_Driver   = [[Gino Munaron]]\n|Third_Country  = Italy\n|Third_Team     = [[Maserati in motorsport|Maserati]]\n|Lapchart       =\n}}\n\nThe '''1960 [[Buenos Aires Grand Prix (motor racing)|Buenos Aires Grand Prix]]''' was a [[Formula Libre]] race over 75 laps of the Parque Sarmient circuit in [[C\u00f3rdoba, Argentina|Cordoba]]. The race was won by [[Maurice Trintignant]] in a [[Cooper T51]].\n\n==Entry list==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%\"\n|-\n! Pos\n! Driver\n! Entrant\n! Constructor\n! Time/Retired\n! Grid\n|-\n! 1\n| {{flagicon|France}} [[Maurice Trintignant]]\n| [[R.R.C. Walker Racing Team]]\n| [[Cooper T51]]-[[Coventry Climax|Climax]]\n| 1:53:50.9, 122.53&nbsp;km/h\n| 2\n|-\n! 2\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Dan Gurney]]\n| [[Owen Racing Organisation]]\n| [[BRM P25]]\n| 1:54:38.5 (+47.6s)\n| 4\n|-\n! 3\n| {