rican Historical Review |volume=74 |number=4 |year=1994 |pages=587\u2013613 |ref=harv|doi=10.2307/2517493 |jstor=2517493 }}\n* {{cite book |last1=Merriman|first1=Roger Bigelow  |authorlink=Roger Bigelow Merriman |title=The Rise of the Spanish Empire in the Old World and the New |location=New York  |year=1918 |url=https://archive.org/search.php?query=Spanish%20%20Merriman |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Olson |first1=James S. |title=Historical Dictionary of the Spanish Empire, 1402\u20131975 |year=1992 |url=https://www.questia.com/library/3767770/historical-dictionary-of-the-spanish-empire-1402-1975 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Paquette |first=Gabriel B |title=Enlightenment, governance, and reform in Spain and its empire, 1759\u20131808  |location=New York |publisher=Palgrave Macmillan 2008 |isbn=978-0230300521 |ref=harv|date=17 January 2008 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Parker |first=Geoffrey |year=1997 |title=The Thirty Years' War |edition= 2nd  |location=New York |publisher=Routledge |isbn=978-0-415-12883-4 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Parker |first=Geoffrey |year=1972 |title=The Army of Flanders and the Spanish Road, 1567\u20131659; the logistics of Spanish victory and defeat in the Low Countries' Wars |location=Cambridge |publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn=978-0-521-08462-8 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Parker |first=Geoffrey|year=1977 |title=The Dutch revolt |location=Cambridge |publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn=978-0-8014-1136-6 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Parker |first=Geoffrey |year=1997 |title=The General Crisis of the Seventeenth Century |location=New York |publisher=Routledge |isbn=978-0-415-16518-1|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |authorlink=J.H. Parry |last=Parry |first=J.H. |title=The Spanish Seaborne Empire |location=Berkeley  |publisher=University of California Press  |year=1966 |isbn=978-0-520-07140-7 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Ramsey |first=John Fraser |year=1973 |title=Spain: The Rise of the First World Power |publisher=University of Alabama Press |isbn=978-0-8173-5704-7 |ref=harv |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/spainriseoffirst0000rams }}\n* {{cite journal |last1=Restall |first1=Matthew |title=The Decline and Fall of the Spanish Empire? |journal=The William and Mary Quarterly |volume=64 |number=1 |year=2007 |pages=183\u2013194 |ref=harv|jstor=4491607 }}\n* {{cite book |editor-last1=Schmidt-Nowara |editor-first1=Christopher |editor-first2=John M. |editor-last2=Nieto Phillips |title=Interpreting Spanish Colonialism: Empires, Nations, and Legends |location=Albuquerque, NM |publisher=University of New Mexico Press |date=2005|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1= Stein |first1= Stanley J. |first2=Barbara H. |last2=Stein |title=Apogee of Empire: Spain and New Spain in the Age of Charles III, 1759-1789  |year=2003 |location=Baltimore |publisher=Johns Hopkins University |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Stradling |first=R. A. |date=1988 |title=Philip IV and the Government of Spain |location=Cambridge |publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn=978-0-521-32333-8|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Studnicki-Gizbert |first=Daviken |date=2007 |title=A Nation upon the Ocean Sea: Portugal's Atlantic Diaspora and the Crisis of the Spanish Empire, 1492\u20131640 |publisher=Oxford University Press |isbn=978-0-19-803911-2|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Thomas |first=Hugh |date=2004 |title=Rivers of Gold: The Rise of the Spanish Empire 1490\u20131522 |publisher=Weidenfeld & Nicolson |isbn=978-0-297-64563-4|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Thomas |first=Hugh |date=1997 |title=The Slave Trade; The History of the Atlantic Slave Trade 1440\u20131870 |location=London |publisher=Papermac |isbn=978-0-333-73147-5|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Vicens Vives |first=Jaime |title=An Economic History of Spain |url=https://archive.org/details/bettycrockersnew00bett_2 |url-access=registration |edition= 3rd revised |location=Princeton  |year=1969|ref=harv|publisher=Princeton, N.J., Princeton University Press }}\n* {{cite book |editor-last=Wright |editor-first=Esmond |date=1984 |title=History of the World, Part II: The last five hundred years |edition= third |location=New York |publisher=Hamlyn Publishing |isbn=978-0-517-43644-8|ref=harv}}\n{{div col end|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons}}\n* [http://libro.uca.edu/payne1/spainport1.htm Library of Iberian Resources Online, Stanley G Payne ''A History of Spain and Portugal'' vol 1 Ch 13 \"The Spanish Empire\"]\n* [https://archive.is/19961226232657/http://www.sonic.net/~doretk/ArchiveARCHIVE/NATIVE%20AMERICAN/TheMestizo-Mexicano-Indi.html The Mestizo-Mexicano-Indian History in the USA]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20061203063044/http://www.knmetv.org/programming/villadeabq.php3 Documentary Film, ''Villa de Albuquerque'']\n* [https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http://es.geocities.com/coloniasesp&date=2009-10-25+03:17:15 The last Spanish colonies] {{in lang|es}}\n* {{Citation |title=Fronteras, identidad, conflicto e interacci\u00f3n. Los Presidios Espa\u00f1oles en el Norte Africano |author=Francisco Jos\u00e9 Calder\u00f3n V\u00e1zquez |year=2008 |language=Spanish |isbn=978-84-691-6786-1 |url=http://www.eumed.net/libros/2008c/433/ |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090214075645/http://eumed.net/libros/2008c/433/ |archivedate=14 February 2009 |df=dmy-all }}\n* [http://international.loc.gov/intldl/drakehtml/rbdkhome.html The Kraus Collection of Sir Francis Drake] at the [[Library of Congress]] contains primary materials on Spanish colonialism.\n\n{{Spanish Empire}}\n{{Colonialism}}\n{{History of Europe}}\n\n[[Category:Christian states]]\n[[Category:Spanish Empire| ]]\n[[Category:Former empires]]\n[[Category:History of European colonialism]]\n[[Category:House of Habsburg|Spain]]\n[[Category:Overseas empires]]\n[[Category:Spanish colonization of the Americas]]\n[[Category:1492 establishments in the Spanish Empire|.]]\n[[Category:1492 establishments in Spain|.]]\n[[Category:1975 disestablishments in Spain|.]]\n[[Category:Spanish Netherlands]]\n[[Category:History of Burgundy]]\n[[Category:History of Calabria]]\n[[Category:History of Campania]]\n[[Category:History of Franche-Comt\u00e9]]\n[[Category:History of Occitanie]]\n[[Category:History of Lombardy]]\n[[Category:Early Modern Luxembourg]]\n[[Category:History of Hauts-de-France]]\n[[Category:2nd millennium in Spain]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the use of the imperial title in medieval Spain|Imperator totius Hispaniae}}\n{{short description|World empire from the 16th to the 19th century}}\n{{pp-semi-sock|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2013}}\n{{Infobox former country\n| common_name            = Spanish Empire\n| native_name            = {{Native name|es|Imperio Espa\u00f1ol}}<br />{{Native name|la|Imperium Hispanicum}}\n| conventional_long_name = Spanish Empire\n| image_flag             = Flag of Cross of Burgundy.svg\n| p1                     = Crown of Castile\n| flag_p1                = Banner of arms crown of Castille Habsbourg style.svg\n| p2                     = Crown of Aragon\n| flag_p2                = Royal Banner of Arag%C3%B3n.svg\n| border_p2              = no\n| p3                     = Emirate of Granada\n| flag_p3                = Royal_Standard_of_Nasrid_Dynasty_Kingdom_of_Grenade.svg\n| border_p3              = no\n| p4                     = Kingdom of Navarre\n| flag_p4                = Bandera de Reino de Navarra.svg\n| p5                     =\n| p6                     = Burgundian Netherlands\n| flag_p6                = Flag of the Low Countries.svg\n| p7                     = Episcopal principality of Utrecht\n| flag_p7                = Flag of the prince-bishopric of Utrecht.svg\n| p8                     = Aztec Empire\n| flag_p8                = Aztec Triple Alliance.png\n| p9                     = Maya Civilization\n| flag_p9                =\n| p10                    = Inca Empire\n| p11                    = Tondo (historical polity){{!}}Tondo\n| flag_p11     